# The ratio вҲҡm_П„/вҲҡm_e = Оө^{-1} = m_П„/m_e = 3478

# This is MUCH too large for the Koide parametrisation (which gives ratio вүҲ 59)
# The three masses don't come from simple powers of Оө вҖ” they come from
# the su(3) weight diagram structure (the 120В° spacing)

# The B-L projection constrains the OVERALL scale but not ОёвӮҖ directly
# ОёвӮҖ is determined by the ANGULAR position on the Koide cone,
# which depends on the specific linear combination of generators

# What the B-L projection DOES determine:
# The cone half-angle = arccos(вҲҡ(2/3)) = 35.26В°
# This IS a consequence of Q = 2/3 (the Koide ratio)
# And Q = 2/3 follows from the su(3) weight structure

print(f"\n  Koide cone half-angle: arccos(вҲҡ(2/3)) = {np.degrees(np.arccos(np.sqrt(2/3))):.4f}В°")
print(f"  This is the angle between the singlet (1,1,1)/вҲҡ3 and")
print(f"  the fundamental weight vectors of su(3).")
print(f"  Q = 2/3 is the GEOMETRIC CONSTRAINT that the mass vector")
print(f"  lives on the su(3) fundamental representation cone.")

